This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on analyzing the variation of features generated by convolutional neural networks (CNNs) with respect to scene factors that occur in natural images. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of principal component analysis (PCA) to visualize the components of the CNN responses. 

The paper also touches upon machine learning (cs.LG) as it discusses the training of CNNs on large image datasets. 

Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is another likely sub-category as the paper discusses the use of CNNs for image analysis. 

Graphics (cs.GR) is also a possible sub-category as the paper uses a large database of 3D CAD models to render images for analysis. 

Finally, neural networks (cs.NE) is another possible sub-category as the paper discusses the use of CNNs for feature extraction and analysis.
